for total year 2009, as shown in the preceding table, all major geographic areas showed sales declines; however, year-on-year sales growth improved each quarter throughout the year. in the fourth quarter of 2009, sales growth of 11.1 percent was broad-based. every major geographic region expanded sales, with strong performances in asia pacific at 22 percent and latin america and canada each at 19 percent. with respect to organic volume, asia pacific led the way at nearly 19 percent for the fourth quarter. korea, china and taiwan posted the most significant increases, driven by a combination of improved local demand along with the pickup in global electronics. organic volumes were flat to slightly down in other geographic regions, which is an improvement versus the levels of decline seen in the first three quarters of 2009. for 2009, international operations represented approximately 63 percent of 3ms sales.
