the pension accumulated benefit obligation represents the actuarial present value of benefits based on employee service and compensation as of the measurement date and does not include an assumption about future compensation levels. the accumulated benefit obligation of the u.s. pension plans was $11.754 billion and $10.769 billion at december31, 2010 and 2009, respectively. the accumulated benefit obligation of the international pension plans was $4.532 billion and $4.279 billion at december2010 and 2009, respectively.
